The CI Failure appears to be because of this  ZooKeeper issue which is unrelated to these frontend changes: 

```py
 77392 [TestNGInvoker-testGetChildrenOnLargeNumChildren()] 
ERROR org.apache.helix.zookeeper.zkclient.ZkClient [] - 
Failed to get children for path /testGetChildrenOnLargeNumChildren 
because of connection loss. Number of children 110000 
exceeds limit 100000, aborting retry.
```

This PR is ready to be merged, approved by @somecodemonkey   
Final commit message:
## Ensure that create cluster button is visible [helix-front]  (#2212)
Verify that current user is logged in after loading all clusters
to ensure that create cluster button is visible in left sidebar

Looks like the existing template is moved, which enables us to use the template automatically like you posted, if I'm understanding it correctly. 
One question: why is the existing template edited? Looks like the guidelines are removed. 

For https://github.com/apache/helix/issues/2215, I disagree that the current template is irrelevant to front-end changes. Tests, backward compatibility, documentations, commits, code qualities should all apply to front-end changes.It shouldn't slow down PR creation, especially after your change to use the templates automatically - comparing to the new template being proposed here, the only extra work is the 3 checkboxes.

This PR is ready to be merged, approved by @qqu0127
